description:
Origin

Tyrone was the product of a genetics program focused on creating super-humans for a company known as "The Hive" which intended to create a super hero group (and secretly also sex slaves).

Tyrone escaped The Hive with others and together they formed the Brats Bizarre

Creation

Tyrone first appeared in the "Brats Bizarre" strip in the 23rd issue of the British anthology comic Toxic, the comic was unfortunately canceled soon afterwards leaving the creator owned comic homeless.

Pat Mills later took the strip to Epic Comics for a four issue mini-series.

Powers

Tyrone can create vacuum bubbles around his enemies to kill them.
name: Tyrone

description:
Origin

Blade was made in a test tube by a company called "The Hive" who were aiming to create a group of loyal super humans that they could control and manipulate.

Blade and others escaped from the Hive and formed a group called "Brats Bizarre"

Creation

Blade first appeared in the "Brats Bizarre" strip in the 23rd issue of the British anthology comic Toxic, the comic was unfortunately canceled soon afterwards leaving the creator owned comic homeless.

Pat Mills later took the strip to Epic Comics for a four issue mini-series.

Powers

Blade can control and manipulate fire, she can shoot flames and throw fireballs.
name: Blade

deck: Ludovic Valley was the father of Jean-Paul Valley and unwillingly passed down the mantle of Azrael after his death.
description:
Creation

Ludovic Valley first appeared in Batman: Sword of Azrael #1 from writer Denny O'Neil and first drawn by Joe Quesada.

Major Story Arcs

Ludovic Valley had been a member of the Order of St. Dumas where he acted as Azrael like his own farther had. He was murdered by Carleton LeHah but managed to contact his son jean-Paul Valley before his death, providing him with funds that he might escape becoming the next Azrael. Jean-Paul misunderstood his father's dying wish however, and took it upon himself to train as the next Azrael.
